AgentDriftStatus.description:
Current drift posture of an agent's deployed model relative to its calibration baseline (governance S2 driftMonitoring). Closed-with-vendor-extension enum (ADR 0082 D-12). Reserved literals: `nominal` (drift signals within calibration window), `watch` (drift trending toward the recalibration threshold but not yet breached), `recalibration-required` (drift exceeded the threshold; agent SHOULD be recalibrated before further use), `demoted` (governance suspended the agent's autonomy until recalibration), `unknown` (no drift observation available â€” typical for newly-declared agents). Vendor extensions MUST use an `x-` prefix.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Current drift posture of an agent's deployed model relative to its calibration baseline (governance S2 driftMonitoring). Closed-with-vendor-extension enum (ADR 0082 D-12). Reserved literals: `nominal` (drift signals within calibration window), `watch` (drift trending toward the recalibration threshold but not yet breached), `recalibration-required` (drift exceeded the threshold; agent SHOULD be recalibrated before further use), `demoted` (governance suspended the agent's autonomy until recalibration), `unknown` (no drift observation available â€” typical for newly-declared agents). Vendor extensions MUST use an `x-` prefix.",
  "examples": [
    "nominal",
    "recalibration-required"
  ],
  "oneOf": [
    {
      "enum": [
        "nominal",
        "watch",
        "recalibration-required",
        "demoted",
        "unknown"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^x-[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$"
    }
  ]
}
 ```
 </details>

AgentShadowModeDivergenceInput.description:
Input parameters for the agent-shadow-mode-divergence report (advanced/advanced-governance.md shadow mode; advanced-governance.md:370-385). Counts and characterises divergence between the shadow agent's outputs and the baseline (human reviewer or production model) over the requested time window.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Input parameters for the agent-shadow-mode-divergence report (advanced/advanced-governance.md shadow mode; advanced-governance.md:370-385). Counts and characterises divergence between the shadow agent's outputs and the baseline (human reviewer or production model) over the requested time window.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "reportType",
    "timeRange"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "agentId": {
      "description": "Optional agent URN to restrict the report to a single shadow agent.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/WosResourceUrn"
    },
    "reportType": {
      "description": "Discriminator literal selecting the agent-shadow-mode-divergence input variant.",
      "const": "agent-shadow-mode-divergence"
    },
    "timeRange": {
      "description": "UTC time window over which divergence comparisons are aggregated.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/TimeRange"
    },
    "workflowUrl": {
      "description": "Author-time workflow URL to scope the report to. Omit to span all visible workflows.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/WorkflowUrl"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

AgentShadowModeDivergenceRow.description:
Per-agent result row for the agent-shadow-mode-divergence report (advanced/advanced-governance.md shadow mode; advanced-governance.md:370-385).

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Per-agent result row for the agent-shadow-mode-divergence report (advanced/advanced-governance.md shadow mode; advanced-governance.md:370-385).",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "agentId",
    "comparisonsCount",
    "divergenceCount",
    "divergenceRate",
    "reportType"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "agentId": {
      "description": "Agent URN this row is attributed to.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/WosResourceUrn"
    },
    "averageDivergenceMagnitude": {
      "description": "Mean normalized disagreement magnitude across diverging comparisons. Method-specific units; consult the workflow's shadow-mode declaration.",
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": 1.0,
      "minimum": 0.0
    },
    "baselineModelIdentifier": {
      "description": "Identifier of the baseline the shadow agent was compared against (`human` for human-reviewer baseline, otherwise a model identifier). Open identifier â€” projected from the agent's `shadowMode.baselineModelIdentifier`.",
      "examples": [
        "human"
      ],
      "type": "string",
      "minLength": 1,
      "x-wos": {
        "openStringKind": "identifier"
      }
    },
    "comparisonsCount": {
      "description": "Number of shadow-vs-baseline comparisons observed within the window.",
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0.0
    },
    "divergenceCount": {
      "description": "Number of comparisons whose normalized disagreement exceeded the agent's `shadowMode.divergenceThreshold`.",
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0.0
    },
    "divergenceRate": {
      "description": "Divergence rate in [0,1] for this agent within the window â€” `divergenceCount / comparisonsCount`.",
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": 1.0,
      "minimum": 0.0
    },
    "reportType": {
      "description": "Discriminator literal selecting the agent-shadow-mode-divergence row variant.",
      "const": "agent-shadow-mode-divergence"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

