ApplicantAiInvolvementSummary.description:
Applicant-facing summary disclosing AI involvement on this case (EU AI Act Art. 13 transparency obligation to the affected person; OMB M-24-10; ai-integration.md Â§12.1-Â§12.2 line 592-604: "For `rights-impacting` workflows, `discloseThatAgentAssisted` MUST be `true`"). Surfaces the FACT of AI involvement and the operational shape that bears on appeal rights â€” agent count, role, narrative-record count for further inquiry, and whether human review covered every agent decision â€” without leaking model identifiers, internal model parameters, or the underlying autonomy enum. Present on `ApplicantCaseDetail` iff the governing workflow's `aiOversight.disclosure.discloseThatAgentAssisted` is true.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Applicant-facing summary disclosing AI involvement on this case (EU AI Act Art. 13 transparency obligation to the affected person; OMB M-24-10; ai-integration.md Â§12.1-Â§12.2 line 592-604: \"For `rights-impacting` workflows, `discloseThatAgentAssisted` MUST be `true`\"). Surfaces the FACT of AI involvement and the operational shape that bears on appeal rights â€” agent count, role, narrative-record count for further inquiry, and whether human review covered every agent decision â€” without leaking model identifiers, internal model parameters, or the underlying autonomy enum. Present on `ApplicantCaseDetail` iff the governing workflow's `aiOversight.disclosure.discloseThatAgentAssisted` is true.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "agentsInvolved",
    "humanReviewedAllAgentDecisions",
    "narrativeRecordCount"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "agentsInvolved": {
      "description": "Agents whose actions contributed to this case, ordered by `roleInDecision` (`primary` first, then `advisory`, then `fallback`). Empty when no agent participated despite the workflow declaring AI capability â€” disclosure on a per-case-actual-involvement basis is the regulatory obligation.",
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/ApplicantAgentSummary"
      }
    },
    "humanReviewedAllAgentDecisions": {
      "description": "True when every agent action on this case was followed by recorded human review per the workflow's review-protocol obligation. False signals that at least one agent action took effect without per-action human review (`autonomous` autonomy with after-the-fact review or sample-based review). Load-bearing for the applicant's ability to assess appeal grounds and for the staff's confidence in the determination chain.",
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "narrativeRecordCount": {
      "description": "Count of narrative-tier provenance records on this case (ai-integration.md Â§13). The applicant uses this as a hint for further inquiry â€” \"there are 3 narrative records about this case\" â€” without exposing the record contents themselves at this projection.",
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0.0
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

ApplicantCaseDetail.description:
Full applicant-visible case projection returned by `GET /api/v1/applicant/cases/{id}`. Wraps a `summary` envelope (the same shape returned by the list endpoint), the applicant-owed open task set, the most recent applicant notifications for this case, and the bounded status timeline. Holds, delegations, review state, governance internals, and other staff-only subresources are NOT exposed; the applicant view is intentionally narrower than staff `WorkflowProcessWithIncludes`.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Full applicant-visible case projection returned by `GET /api/v1/applicant/cases/{id}`. Wraps a `summary` envelope (the same shape returned by the list endpoint), the applicant-owed open task set, the most recent applicant notifications for this case, and the bounded status timeline. Holds, delegations, review state, governance internals, and other staff-only subresources are NOT exposed; the applicant view is intentionally narrower than staff `WorkflowProcessWithIncludes`.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "openTasks",
    "recentNotifications",
    "statusTimeline",
    "summary"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "aiInvolvement": {
      "description": "EU AI Act Art. 13 / OMB M-24-10 disclosure of AI involvement on this case (ai-integration.md Â§12.1-Â§12.2 line 592-604). Present iff the governing workflow's `aiOversight.disclosure.discloseThatAgentAssisted` is true. Exposes the FACT of AI involvement and the operational shape (agent count, role, human-review coverage, narrative-record count) â€” never internal model identifiers or autonomy enums. Closes the structural disclosure gap on the applicant-facing surface.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/ApplicantAiInvolvementSummary"
    },
    "openTasks": {
      "description": "Applicant-owed tasks currently in `pending` or `drafted` status, ordered by `deadline` ascending then `createdAt` ascending. Bounded set per case; the dedicated subresource `GET /api/v1/applicant/cases/{id}/tasks` is the cursor-paginated form for cases with many historical tasks.",
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/ApplicantTaskSummary"
      }
    },
    "recentNotifications": {
      "description": "Most recent applicant notifications scoped to this case, ordered by `createdAt` descending. Bounded by server-side cap (typically the most recent 20). Full feed at `GET /api/v1/applicant/notifications`.",
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/ApplicantNotificationListItem"
      }
    },
    "statusTimeline": {
      "description": "Applicant-visible status timeline for this case, ordered by `occurredAt` ascending. Bounded set per case (governed events the applicant has authority to see).",
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/ApplicantStatusTimelineEntry"
      }
    },
    "summary": {
      "description": "Case summary envelope â€” same shape as the list-view item, repeated for self-containment.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/ApplicantCaseSummary"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

ApplicantCaseSummary.description:
Lightweight applicant-facing case projection for list views. Distinct from staff `instance.schema.json#/$defs/WorkflowProcess` â€” the applicant view hides governance internals (delegations, review state, hold rationale) and surfaces only the fields the applicant has authority to see. Carries the case URN, governing workflow, lifecycle posture, last-update timestamp, and an `actionNeeded` flag indicating whether at least one applicant-owed task is in `pending` or `drafted` status.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Lightweight applicant-facing case projection for list views. Distinct from staff `instance.schema.json#/$defs/WorkflowProcess` â€” the applicant view hides governance internals (delegations, review state, hold rationale) and surfaces only the fields the applicant has authority to see. Carries the case URN, governing workflow, lifecycle posture, last-update timestamp, and an `actionNeeded` flag indicating whether at least one applicant-owed task is in `pending` or `drafted` status.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "actionNeeded",
    "createdAt",
    "id",
    "lifecycleState",
    "updatedAt",
    "workflowUrl"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "actionNeeded": {
      "description": "True when at least one applicant-owed task on this case is currently in `pending` or `drafted` status (i.e. the applicant has work outstanding). Computed server-side.",
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "continuationOfServicesActive": {
      "description": "True when the case is operating under a continuation-of-services policy (governance Â§3.6 â€” `AppealMechanism.continuationOfServices`; workflow-governance.md:154-158). Surfaces the existence of the policy without leaking the underlying rationale; the applicant has unambiguous authority to see this fact because it directly bears on whether benefits continue during appeal.",
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "continuationOfServicesEndsAt": {
      "description": "Absolute UTC RFC 3339 timestamp at which the active continuation-of-services window closes, or the literal `never` for indefinite continuation (governance Â§3.6; ADR 0082 D-10 sentinel pattern). Present only when `continuationOfServicesActive == true`.",
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "date-time"
        },
        {
          "const": "never"
        }
      ]
    },
    "createdAt": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 timestamp when the case was created.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "id": {
      "description": "Stable public URN for this workflow process.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/WosResourceUrn"
    },
    "lifecycleState": {
      "description": "Closed lifecycle posture for this case (projected from `instance.schema.json`).",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/LifecycleState"
    },
    "title": {
      "description": "Short human-readable case label suitable for list rendering. Sourced from the workflow's case-file `caseLabel` mapping when configured; falls back to a workflow-name-based default. Open prose â€” rendering concern.",
      "examples": [
        "Application for benefits adjudication"
      ],
      "type": "string",
      "minLength": 1,
      "x-wos": {
        "openStringKind": "prose"
      }
    },
    "updatedAt": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 timestamp of the most recent applicant-visible update.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "workflowUrl": {
      "description": "Absolute URI of the governing Workflow Document.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/WorkflowUrl"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

