DashboardRangeOptions.description:
Query fields for `GET /api/v1/dashboard/summary`, `/lifecycle-rollup`, `/sla-breaches`, and `/recent-activity`. All fields are optional â€” a request with no parameters returns the server's default look-back window scoped to the calling actor's tenant. The contract carries no `cursor`/`limit` pagination because dashboard responses are count-style cached envelopes (ADR 0082 D-7), not lists.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Query fields for `GET /api/v1/dashboard/summary`, `/lifecycle-rollup`, `/sla-breaches`, and `/recent-activity`. All fields are optional â€” a request with no parameters returns the server's default look-back window scoped to the calling actor's tenant. The contract carries no `cursor`/`limit` pagination because dashboard responses are count-style cached envelopes (ADR 0082 D-7), not lists.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "since": {
      "description": "Inclusive UTC RFC 3339 lower bound on the event range used for `slaBreaches` and `recentActivity` computations (ADR 0069). When omitted the server applies a default look-back window (typically 30 days).",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "tenantScope": {
      "description": "Deployment tenant scope filter (ADR 0068 D-1.1 â€” Proposed). MUST agree with the `X-WOS-Tenant` header when both are present; the server rejects mismatches with `WOS-1422`.",
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^[a-z][a-z0-9-]{0,62}$"
    },
    "until": {
      "description": "Exclusive UTC RFC 3339 upper bound on the event range. Defaults to the server's wall clock when omitted.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

DashboardSummary.description:
Top-level dashboard rollup returned by `GET /api/v1/dashboard/summary`. Composes the three section rollups (`LifecycleStateRollup`, `SlaBreachSummary`, `RecentActivitySummary`) plus a single envelope-level `asOf` timestamp so consumers can decide whether to refresh. Per ADR 0082 D-7 the response is a cached `asOf`-stamped envelope rather than a cursor-paginated list â€” counts on append-only logs are best-effort and cached aggressively at the server.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Top-level dashboard rollup returned by `GET /api/v1/dashboard/summary`. Composes the three section rollups (`LifecycleStateRollup`, `SlaBreachSummary`, `RecentActivitySummary`) plus a single envelope-level `asOf` timestamp so consumers can decide whether to refresh. Per ADR 0082 D-7 the response is a cached `asOf`-stamped envelope rather than a cursor-paginated list â€” counts on append-only logs are best-effort and cached aggressively at the server.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "asOf",
    "lifecycle",
    "recentActivity",
    "slaBreaches"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "asOf": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 envelope-level timestamp the summary was computed (ADR 0082 D-7). Section-level `asOf` fields MAY be earlier than this when the server caches sections at different cadences.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "lifecycle": {
      "description": "Closed map of case counts by lifecycle posture.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/LifecycleStateRollup"
    },
    "recentActivity": {
      "description": "Count of recent governed events grouped by `RecentActivityEventClass`.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/RecentActivitySummary"
    },
    "since": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 inclusive lower bound the rollup was computed against. Echoed from `DashboardRangeOptions.since` when supplied. Omitted when the server applied its default look-back window.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "slaBreaches": {
      "description": "Count and timestamp envelope of SLA breaches in the requested range.",
      "$ref": "#/$defs/SlaBreachSummary"
    },
    "tenantScope": {
      "description": "Deployment tenant the rollup was computed for (ADR 0068 D-1.1 â€” Proposed). Single DNS label: lowercase ASCII letter first, then lowercase letters, digits, or hyphen, length 1 to 63. Echoed from the request when supplied; resolved from `X-WOS-Tenant` otherwise. Omitted only when the server has not yet adopted ADR 0068 scope-stamping.",
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^[a-z][a-z0-9-]{0,62}$"
    },
    "until": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 exclusive upper bound the rollup was computed against. Echoed from `DashboardRangeOptions.until` when supplied. Defaults to the server's `asOf` clock when absent.",
      "type": "string",
