SlaBreachSummary.description:
Counted SLA breaches across cases in the requested range, returned by `GET /api/v1/dashboard/sla-breaches` and embedded in `DashboardSummary.slaBreaches`. SLA breach semantics (governance S10.3, S10.4) are workflow-defined; the dashboard projects the count and the timestamp envelope of breach occurrences. Per ADR 0082 D-7 the response is a cached `asOf`-stamped envelope, not a list.

 <details><summary>JSON schema</summary>

 ```json
{
  "description": "Counted SLA breaches across cases in the requested range, returned by `GET /api/v1/dashboard/sla-breaches` and embedded in `DashboardSummary.slaBreaches`. SLA breach semantics (governance S10.3, S10.4) are workflow-defined; the dashboard projects the count and the timestamp envelope of breach occurrences. Per ADR 0082 D-7 the response is a cached `asOf`-stamped envelope, not a list.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "asOf",
    "count"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "asOf": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 timestamp the breach summary was computed.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "count": {
      "description": "Total SLA breach occurrences in the requested range. Best-effort per ADR 0082 D-7; counts on append-only logs are cached, not transactionally consistent.",
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0.0
    },
    "earliestBreachAt": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 timestamp of the earliest SLA breach in the requested range. Omitted when `count` is zero.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "latestBreachAt": {
      "description": "UTC RFC 3339 timestamp of the latest SLA breach in the requested range. Omitted when `count` is zero.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
 ```
 </details>

